The participant was positioned supine, feet-first and fitted with a commercial, single channel chest coil (Polarean Xenoview, Raleigh-Durham, NC). Three 129Xe scans were obtained (A calibration, ventilation, and gas exchange acquisition); each under a 10 s breath hold29. The calibration scan was acquired to calculate the center frequency, transmit voltage, and echo time (TE) where alveolar-capillary membrane (mem) and red blood cell (RBC) compartments are 90\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
